TITLE: Evaluating and Comparing Results in Casper Contract Tests
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to retrieve and verify the results of a Casper contract execution in a test environment. It demonstrates querying a value and comparing it to an expected result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/developers/writing-onchain-code/testing-contracts.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
let incremented_count = builder
    .query(None, count_key, &[])
    .expect("should be stored value.")
    .as_cl_value()
    .expect("should be cl value.")
    .clone()
    .into_t::<i32>()
    .expect("should be i32.");

assert_eq!(incremented_count, 1);
```

