TITLE: Implementing Entry Points in Casper Contract Call Function
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to define a call function and add entry points to a Casper smart contract. It initializes a counter value and sets up public entry points for getting and incrementing the counter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/docs/developers/writing-onchain-code/simple-contract.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[no_mangle]
pub extern "C" fn call() {
    // Initialize the count to 0 locally
    let count_start = storage::new_uref(0_i32);
    // Create the entry points for this contract
    let mut counter_entry_points = EntryPoints::new();

    counter_entry_points.add_entry_point(EntryPoint::new(
        ENTRY_POINT_COUNTER_GET,
        Vec::new(),
        CLType::I32,
        EntryPointAccess::Public,
