DESCRIPTION: Shows how to sign a deploy using a Ledger hardware wallet connected via WebUSB. It establishes a connection using `@ledgerhq/hw-transport-webusb`, initializes the Casper Ledger app (`@zondax/ledger-casper`), converts the deploy to bytes, and calls the `ledgerApp.sign` method with the BIP path and deploy bytes to get the signature. Depends on the Ledger transport and app libraries, `DeployUtil` from `casper-js-sdk`, and the account index.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/docs/resources/advanced/list-cspr.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
