TITLE: Installing a Contract with Multiple Authorization Keys in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This Rust code demonstrates building and executing a deploy item to install a contract (`CONTRACT_WASM`). The installation is authorized by two keys: `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ADDR` and `account_addr_1`. It sets the payment, specifies both authorization keys, the target address (`DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ADDR`), and uses the `CONTRACT_WASM` session code. The test builder executes the request and expects it to succeed.
