TITLE: Defining Template Entry Points in a Casper Factory Contract (Rust)
DESCRIPTION: This Rust code shows how to define potential entry points (`INCREASE_ENTRY_POINT`, `DECREASE_ENTRY_POINT`) within the main session logic of a factory contract. They are marked with `EntryPointAccess::Template` and `EntryPointType::Contract`. This declaration makes these entry point definitions available as templates that can be included in the contracts created by the factory's installer entry points.
