TITLE: Transferring NFT Tokens Between Accounts - casper-cep78-js-client - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Presents how to transfer an NFT from one account (source) to another (target) using the transfer method. You must specify the tokenId, source public key, and target public key. The session code usage depends on the contract's lookup mode, and transfer requires sender's keys and an RPC URL. A deploy hash is returned that can be checked for transfer completion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/docs/resources/tokens/cep78/js-tutorial.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```

  const transferDeploy = cc.transfer(
    {
      tokenId: "0",
      source: FAUCET_KEYS.publicKey,
      target: USER1_KEYS.publicKey,
    },
    { useSessionCode: true },
    "13000000000",
    FAUCET_KEYS.publicKey,
    [FAUCET_KEYS]
  );

  const transferDeployHash = await transferDeploy.send("http://localhost:11101/rpc");

```

