TITLE: Exporting Public Key and Account Hash in Python with pycspr - Python
DESCRIPTION: Obtains hex-encoded public key and account hash from a pycspr keypair. Utilizes pycspr.crypto.cl_checksum and cl_operations for conversion. Expects a previously created keypair object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-1.5.X/developers/dapps/sdk/client-library-usage.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import pycspr.crypto

publicKeyBytes = keypair.account_key
publicKeyHex = pycspr.crypto.cl_checksum.encode(publicKeyBytes)
accountHashBytes = pycspr.crypto.cl_operations.get_account_hash(publicKeyBytes)
accountHashHex = pycspr.crypto.cl_checksum.encode(accountHashBytes)
```

