TITLE: Calling Smart Contract Entry Points via Session Code - Rust
DESCRIPTION: These two lines demonstrate how session code invokes methods within an existing contract. runtime::call_contract is used with the contract hash, entry point name, and supplied runtime args. The first line retrieves a counter's current value (as u32); the second increments the counter (return type is unit). These patterns enable composition of contract logic and chaining of contract or session logic in Rust.
