TITLE: Verifying Intersection Result in Named Keys - Casper Test Framework - Rust
DESCRIPTION: This snippet queries the result of a contract execution saved in an account's named keys and asserts the expected intersection of authorization keys. It retrieves the receipt, performs a query, extracts CLValue data, and compares the actual intersection against expectations. Dependencies are test builder API, expected account data, and correct constants for key names. The input is the post-deploy builder state; output is an assertion of intersection correctness. Main limitation: expects only a single intersection scenario.
