TITLE: Transferring CSPR with Python pycspr SDK - Python
DESCRIPTION: Creates, signs, and submits a Casper transfer deploy with pycspr. Requires configuration of client, recipient key, deploy parameters, and keypair approval. Prints the deploy hash upon submission. All parameters, such as node address and chain name, must match the target Casper network.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-1.5.X/developers/dapps/sdk/client-library-usage.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import pycspr

client = NodeClient(NodeConnection(host = "NODE_ADDRESS", port_rpc = 7777))
recipientPublicKeyHex = "01e8c84f4fbb58d37991ef373c08043a45c44cd7f499453fa2bd3e141cc0113b3c"
recipientPublicKeyBytes = pycspr.crypto.cl_checksum.decode(recipientPublicKeyHex)

deployParams = pycspr.create_deploy_parameters(
    account = keypair,
    chain_name = "casper" # or "casper-test" for Testnet
)

deploy = pycspr.create_transfer(
    params = deployParams,
    amount = int(2.5e9), # Minimum transfer: 2.5 CSPR
    target = recipientPublicKeyBytes
)

deploy.approve(keypair)
client.send_deploy(deploy)
print(deploy.hash.hex())
```

