TITLE: Defining Trie Chunking Data Structures in Rust
DESCRIPTION: These Rust structs and enums define the types used for requesting and transferring parts of the global state trie. `TrieOrChunkId` identifies a specific trie node or chunk. `TrieOrChunk` is an enum that holds either the raw trie data (`Bytes`) or a `ChunkWithProof`, which includes the chunk data and an `IndexedMerkleProof` for verification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/concepts/design/networking-protocol.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
```rust
struct TrieOrChunkId(u64, Digest);

enum TrieOrChunk {
    Trie(Bytes),
    ChunkWithProof(ChunkWithProof),
}

struct ChunkWithProof {
    proof: IndexedMerkleProof,
    chunk: Bytes,
}

struct IndexedMerkleProof {
    index: u64,
    count: u64,
    merkle_proof: Vec<Digest>,
}
```
