DESCRIPTION: This command updates the deployment and key management thresholds to create a multi-signature scheme. The update_thresholds.wasm session is used to set specific thresholds for account actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-1.5.X/resources/advanced/multi-sig/multi-sig-workflow.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
casper-client put-deploy \
--node-address https://node.testnet.casper.network \
--chain-name casper-test \
--payment-amount 500000000 \
--secret-key $PATH/secret_key.pem \
--session-path target/wasm32-unknown-unknown/release/update_thresholds.wasm \
--session-arg "deployment_threshold:u8='2'" \
--session-arg "key_management_threshold:u8='3'"
```

