TITLE: Querying Auction Bid Status with Casper Client and jq - Bash
DESCRIPTION: This Bash snippet uses `casper-client get-auction-info` piped to `jq` to filter bids by a specified public key. This allows a validator to check their bid status, such as 'inactive', after suspected eviction. Dependencies: `casper-client`, `jq`. The `<public_key>` placeholder must be replaced with the validator's hexadecimal public key. The output is a subset of the full auction state JSON corresponding to the selected public key. Limitations: Assumes the node's RPC port is live and returns valid auction state data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-1.5.X/operators/becoming-a-validator/recovering.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
casper-client get-auction-info | jq '.result.auction_state.bids[] | select( .public_key == "<public_key>")'
```

