TITLE: Defining Template Entry Points for Counter Factory in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This code defines the non-installer entry points (increment and decrement) in the factory contract, marking them with EntryPointAccess::Template and EntryPointType::Contract. This is necessary for these entry points to be available in the produced counter contracts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/developers/writing-onchain-code/factory-pattern.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
let entry_point: EntryPoint = EntryPoint::new(
    INCREASE_ENTRY_POINT.to_string(),
    Parameters::new(),
    CLType::Unit,
    EntryPointAccess::Template,
    EntryPointType::Contract,
);
entry_points.add_entry_point(entry_point);
let entry_point: EntryPoint = EntryPoint::new(
    DECREASE_ENTRY_POINT.to_string(),
    Parameters::new(),
    CLType::Unit,
    EntryPointAccess::Template,
    EntryPointType::Contract,
);
```

