TITLE: Integrating Query Component into App (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: Updates the main `App.jsx` component to include the newly created `Query` component. It imports `Query` and renders it alongside the `UpdateMessage` component, conditionally based on the presence of the `publicKey`. The `publicKey` is passed as a prop to the `Query` component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/docs/developers/dapps/template-frontend.md#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import React from "react";
import Connect from "./Connect";
import UpdateMessage from "./UpdateMessage";
// highlight-next-line-green
import Query from "./Query";
import './App.css'

function App() {
    const [publicKey, setPublicKey] = React.useState(null);
    return (
        <>
            <Connect setPublicKey={ setPublicKey } />
            <div>
                {publicKey !== null && (<>
                    Wallet connected: {publicKey}<br/>
                    <UpdateMessage publicKey={ publicKey } />
                    // highlight-next-line-green
                    <Query publicKey={ publicKey } />
                </>)}
            </div>
        </>
    );
}
```

