TITLE: Defining Payment Breakdown Schema in JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON schema snippet specifies the structure required to describe payment transactions in a system. It mandates the inclusion of a 'source', representing the payment source purse, which must reference a predefined schema component 'URef'. The code snippet details necessary structure using JSON schema properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/condor/jsonrpc-comp/rpc-2.0/schema/PaymentInfo.json.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "description": "Breakdown of payments made to cover the cost.",
    "type": "object",
    "required": [
        "source"
    ],
    "properties": {
        "source": {
            "description": "Source purse used for payment of the transaction.",
            "allOf": [
                {
                    "$ref": "#/components/schemas/URef"
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
```

