TITLE: Describing ChecksumRegistry Serialization (Casper Network)
DESCRIPTION: Describes the ChecksumRegistry, which holds checksums. It serializes as a BTreeMap where keys are checksum names (strings) and values are digests (hashes). The serialization follows the standard BTreeMap format: u32 count followed by serialized string keys and digest values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/concepts/serialization/types.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: Text
CODE:
```
## ChecksumRegistry {#checksum-registry}

The checksum registry. It serializes as a `BTreeMap` where the first 4 bytes represent a `u32` value describing the number of checksum names as strings and [digests](#digest) held within. The remainder consists of a repeating pattern of serialized strings and then digests of the length dictated by the first four bytes.
```

