TITLE: Querying Named Keys and State on Casper Chain - Bash
DESCRIPTION: These commands demonstrate querying the Casper chain for named keys and stored values using casper-client query-global-state and the -q argument. Parameters include --state-root-hash, --key (the account hash), and -q (the named key or path). Outputs are JSON representations of contract/named-key state. Examples show retrieving the counter contract, its count variable, and querying a deploy using its hash.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/docs/resources/beginner/counter/walkthrough.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
casper-client query-global-state --node-address http://localhost:11101 \
    --state-root-hash [STATE_ROOT_HASH] \
    --key [ACCOUNT_HASH] -q "counter"
```

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
casper-client query-global-state --node-address http://localhost:11101 \
    --state-root-hash [STATE_ROOT_HASH] \
    --key [ACCOUNT_HASH] -q "counter/count"
```

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
casper-client query-global-state --node-address http://localhost:11101 \
    --state-root-hash [STATE_ROOT_HASH] --key deploy-[DEPLOY_HASH]
```

