TITLE: Defining Node Peer Entry Schema with JSON Schema in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a JSON schema for a node peer entry object, specifying required fields ('address' and 'node_id') and restricting additional properties. Intended for use in validation workflows, it ensures that each node peer entry conforms to the expected format. Dependencies include a JSON Schema validator (such as Ajv), and the schema expects input as a JSON object containing 'node_id' and 'address' as strings; any extraneous properties will be rejected.
