TITLE: Generating Public Keys from Secret Key with OpenSSL
DESCRIPTION: Commands to generate the public_key.pem and public_key_hex files from an existing secret_key.pem file using OpenSSL. The second command adds the '01' prefix for Ed25519 keys.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/docs/concepts/accounts-and-keys.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
openssl pkey -in secret_key.pem -pubout -out public_key.pem

{ echo -n 01; openssl pkey -outform DER -pubout -in "secret_key.pem" | tail -c +13 | openssl base64 | openssl base64 -d | hexdump -ve '/1 "%02x" ' | tr -d "/n"; } > public_key_hex
```

