TITLE: Describing BTreeSet Serialization (Casper Network)
DESCRIPTION: Describes the serialization format for a BTreeSet on the Casper network. It begins with a u32 representing the number of values in the set, followed by the serialized values repeated according to the count.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/concepts/serialization/types.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Text
CODE:
```
## BTreeSet {#btreeset}

A `BTreeSet` is a method of storing a set of values within a Casper network. They serialize with the first 4 bytes representing a `u32` value describing the number of values held within. The remainder consists of a repeating series of values of the length dictated by the first four bytes.
```

