TITLE: Serializing Operation Structure
DESCRIPTION: Describes the `Operation` structure, representing an operation (Read, Write, Add, NoOp) performed during deploy execution. It contains a `key` (formatted string, serialized as `String`) and a `kind` (OpKind, serialized as a single byte tag: 0=Read, 1=Write, 2=Add, 3=NoOp).
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/concepts/serialization/types.md#2025-04-22_snippet_34

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
An operation performed while executing a deploy. It contains:

-   `key`: The formatted string of the key, serialized as a [`String`](./primitives.md#clvalue-string).

-   `kind`: OpKind, The type of operation performed. It serializes as a single byte based on the following table:

|OpKind|Serialization|
|------|-------------|
|Read  | 0           |
|Write | 1           |
|Add   | 2           |
|NoOp  | 3           |
```

