TITLE: Defining Trie and Chunk Related Structures in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Defines structures related to trie chunking in the Casper network, including TrieOrChunkId, TrieOrChunk, ChunkWithProof, and IndexedMerkleProof.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/docs/concepts/design/networking-protocol.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
struct TrieOrChunkId(u64, Digest);

enum TrieOrChunk {
    Trie(Bytes),
    ChunkWithProof(ChunkWithProof),
}

struct ChunkWithProof {
    proof: IndexedMerkleProof,
    chunk: Bytes,
}

struct IndexedMerkleProof {
    index: u64,
    count: u64,
    merkle_proof: Vec<Digest>,
}
```

