TITLE: Describing BlockSignatures Structure (Casper Network)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the BlockSignatures structure, which holds signatures for a block, its hash, and era ID. It exists in two versions (V1 and V2), indicated by a prefixed u8 tag (0 for V1, 1 for V2), detailing how each version is serialized.
SOURCE: https://github.com/casper-network/docs-redux/blob/dev/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/concepts/serialization/types.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Text
CODE:
```
## BlockSignatures {#block-signatures}

A collection of signatures for a single block, along with the associated block's hash and era ID.

There are two possible versions for `BlockSignatures`, with a prefixed `u8` tag describing which version it is.

-   [`BlockSignaturesV1`](#block-signatures-v1) serializes as a `u8` of 0 followed by the `BlockSignaturesV1`.

-   [`BlockSignaturesV2`](#block-signatures-v2) serializes as a `u8` of 1 followed by the `BlockSignaturesV2`.
```

