TITLE: Defining Runtime Arguments for Redelegation Deploy in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Constructs a `RuntimeArgs` object specifically for a redelegation operation. It includes the `delegator`, the original `validator`, the `new_validator` public keys, and the `amount` (in motes). This differs from standard delegation/undelegation by adding the `new_validator` parameter. Depends on `RuntimeArgs`, `CLPublicKey`, and `CLValueBuilder` from `casper-js-sdk`.
